id Harbour Jr., Frankenstein \n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Hellboy (2019 film)|Hellboy]]''\n| [[Hellboy]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2020\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Black Widow (2020 film)|Black Widow]]''\n| [[Red Guardian#Alexei Shostakov|Alexei Shostakov / Red Guardian]]\n| Post-production\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Extraction (2020 film)|Extraction]]''\n| TBA\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"|Year\n! scope=\"col\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\"|Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| 1999\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Law & Order]]'' \n| Mike\n| Episode: \"Patsy\"\n|-\n| 2002\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| Terry Jessup\n| Episode: \"Dolls\"\n|-\n| 2003\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Hack (TV series)|Hack]]''\n| Christopher Clark\n| Episode: \"Presumed Guilty\"\n|-\n| 2004\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]''\n| Wesley John Kenderson\n| Episode: \"Silver Lining\"\n|-\n| 2006\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Book of Daniel (TV series)|The Book of Daniel]]''\n| Kevin Warwick\n| Episode: \"Acceptance\"\n|-\n| 2007\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Unit]]''\n| Gary Weber\n| Episode: \"Five Brothers\"\n|-\n| 2008\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Law & Order''\n| Jay Carlin\n| Episode: \"Submission\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2009\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Law & Order: Criminal Intent''\n| Paul Devildis\n| Episode: \"Family Values\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Lie to Me (TV series)|Lie to Me]]''\n| Frank Ambrose\n| Episode: \"The Better Half\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Royal Pains]]''\n| Dan Samuels\n| Episode: \"It's Like Jamais Vu All Over Again\"\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Pan Am (TV series)|Pan Am]]''\n| Roger Anderson\n| 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Midnight Sun''\n| Ethan Davies \n| Unsold NBC TV pilot\n|-\n| 2012\u20132014\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Newsroom (U.S. TV series)|The Newsroom]]''\n| Elliot Hirsch\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Elementary (TV series)|Elementary]]''\n| Dr. Mason Baldwin\n| Episode: \"Lesser Evils\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Rake (U.S. TV series)|Rake]]''\n| David Potter\n| 11 episodes\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Manhattan (TV series)|Manhattan]]''\n| Dr. Reed Akley\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[State of Affairs (TV series)|State of Affairs]]''\n| David Patrick\n| 13 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Banshee (TV series)|Banshee]]''\n| Robert Dalton\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Crisis in Six Scenes]]''\n| Vic\n| Episode: \"#1.2\"\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Stranger Things]]''\n| [[Jim Hopper (Stranger Things)|Jim Hopper]]\n| Main role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Drunk History]]''\n| Vietnam Memorial Head\n| Episode: \"Underdogs\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Animals (U.S. TV series)|Animals]]''\n| Hawk (voice)\n| Episode: \"Roachella\"\n|-\n| 2019\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n| Himself (host)\n| Episode: \"David Harbour/[[Camila Cabello]]\" \n|-\n| TBA\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Simpsons]]''\n| Undercover Mr. Burns\n| Voice; Episode: \"Undercover Burns\"\n|}\n\n===Theatre===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"|Year\n! scope=\"col\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\"|Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| 1999\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Rainmaker (play)|The Rainmaker]]''\n| Noah Curry\n| \n|-\n| 2001\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Invention of Love]]''\n| Moses John Jackson\n| \n|-\n| 2005\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?]]''\n| Nick\n|\n|-\n| 2006\u20132007\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Coast of Utopia]]: Part 1 \u2013 Voyage''\n| Nicholas Stankevich\n| \n|-\n| 2006\u20132007\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Coast of Utopia]]: Part 2 \u2013 Shipwreck''\n| George Herwegh\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Coast of Utopia]]: Part 3 \u2013 Salvage''\n| Doctor at the Seashore\n| \n|-